  "prompt": "What is a suitable inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Treutlen County GA?",
  "response": "Finding a suitable inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Treutlen County, GA, depends on your specific needs, budget, and preferences. While Treutlen County itself may have limited options, nearby counties and cities in Georgia offer reputable facilities. Here are a few notable rehab centers in the general region:\n\n### 1. **Willowbrooke at Tanner (Villa Rica, GA)**  \n   - Located about 2.5 hours from Treutlen County.  \n   - Offers inpatient detox, residential treatment, and outpatient programs.  \n   - Specializes in treating addiction and co-occurring mental health disorders.  \n   - Contact: (770) 812-3551  \n\n### 2. **Ridgeview Institute (Smyrna, GA)**  \n   - Approximately 2.5 hours from Treutlen County.  \n   - Provides inpatient and outpatient addiction treatment services.  \n   - Offers detox, dual diagnosis treatment, and aftercare planning.  \n   - Contact: (770) 434-4567  \n\n### 3. **Parkwood Healthcare (Statesboro, GA)**  \n   - Located about 1.5 hours from Treutlen County.  \n   - Offers intensive outpatient programs (IOP) and referrals for inpatient care.  \n   - Focuses on personalized treatment plans for addiction recovery.  \n   - Contact: (912) 764-6276  \n\n### 4. **Hope House of Augusta (Augusta, GA)**  \n   - Approximately 2 hours from Treutlen County.  \n   - Specializes in inpatient treatment for women struggling with addiction.  \n   - Provides trauma-informed care and family support services.  \n   - Contact: (706-737-7799  \n\n### 5. **Riverside Counseling Center (Macon, GA)**  \n   - Located about 1.5 hours from Treutlen County.  \n   - Offers inpatient and outpatient addiction treatment programs.  \n   - Focuses on holistic recovery and relapse prevention.  \n   - Contact: (478) 746-5128  \n\n### Factors to Consider When Choosing a Rehab Center:  \n- **Accreditation and Licensing:** Ensure the facility is licensed and accredited by reputable organizations.  \n- **Treatment Approach:** Look for programs that align with your needs (e.g., detox, dual diagnosis, faith-based).  \n- **Insurance and Cost:** Verify if they accept your insurance or offer payment plans.  \n- **Location:** Decide if you prefer a center close to home or one farther away for a fresh start.  \n\n### Additional Resources:  \n- **SAMHSA Treatment Locator**: [https://findtreatment.samhsa.gov/](https://findtreatment.samhsa.gov/)  \n- **Georgia Department of Behavioral Health and Developmental Disabilities (DBHDD)**: [https://dbhdd.georgia.gov/](https://dbhdd.georgia.gov/)  \n\nIt\u2019s advisable to contact the facilities directly to discuss your specific situation and determine the best fit. If you need immediate assistance, consider reaching out to a local healthcare provider or addiction hotline for guidance.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
